      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0023.b001",
      "level": 1,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "9. End Step",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0023.b002",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "During the End Step, if you are on an ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Unexplored",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " tile, it simply be-comes ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Explored",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". This means that if you’re already on an Explored tile, nothing happens.During the first game session, knowing which tiles are Explored is easy: it’s basically all the tiles revealed on the table. The rest of the Map tiles are Unexplored. However, once you play a few more game sessions, saving the game in between, it will become a bit tougher to keep track of. That’s why it’s important to remember how to save the Map properly (see Saving the Campaign below).After you resolve the End Step, proceed to the next Campaign Round.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "icon",
          "symbol_id": "sym.board_tile_a",
          "alt": "Board_tile_a"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0023.b003",
      "level": 1,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Additional Voyage Rules",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0023.b004",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "This section covers all the additional rules governing the Voyage Phase that are not specifically tied to any of the Campaign Round Steps.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "icon",
          "symbol_id": "sym.board_tile_c",
          "alt": "Board_tile_c"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0023.b005",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Saving the Campaign",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0023.b006",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Aeon Trespass: Odyssey",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " is an odyssey of a game. You won’t finish it in one game session. You won’t finish it in two. In fact, a single Cycle will take you dozens of hours. To manage that, you will need to periodically ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "save the campaign",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". This section provides the rules on how to do it.At the end of any Campaign Round Step, you may decide to save your game progress and end your current game session. We advise saving at the end of the End Step so that you can begin your next game at the start of a new day. To save your game, take out the Argo Sheet and perform the following steps:Note the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "number and letter",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " of your current ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Story card",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " along with the number of gathered  tokens (in parentheses).Note the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "number and letter",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " of your current ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Doom card",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " along with the number of gathered  tokens (in parentheses).Note the number of the current Map tile (the one the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Argo",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " is on).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
